[2026-03-18T12:38:20.588Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RgM3zvCunojH3kPm4PviZ5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me compile the complete report. I have all the key information needed.\n\n## Exploration Complete - Full Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the codebase. Here's the comprehensive analysis:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **CONNECTION.TS - FULL CONTENTS**\n\nFile: `/packages/worker/src/connection.ts` (214 lines)\n\nThis file implements the WebSocket-based connection between a Worker and the Orchestrator with automatic reconnection logic.\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Exponential backoff reconnection**: Starts at 1s, doubles up to max 30s\n- **Heartbeat mechanism**: 30s interval to keep connection alive\n- **Message parsing**: Uses protocol from `@dac-cloud/shared`\n- **Callback-based message handling**: `onAssign`, `onCancel`, `onShutdown`\n- **Graceful disconnection**: Cleans up timers and WebSocket connections\n\n**Reconnection Logic (lines 186-197):**\n```typescript\nprivate scheduleReconnect(): void {\n  if (this.shuttingDown) return;\n  this.logger.info({ delayMs: this.reconnectDelay }, 'Scheduling reconnect');\n  \n  this.reconnectTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n    this.connect();\n  }, this.reconnectDelay);\n  \n  // Exponential backoff\n  this.reconnectDelay = Math.min(this.reconnectDelay * 2, MAX_RECONNECT_DELAY_MS);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **EXISTING LOGGING PATTERNS**\n\n**Logger Library:** `pino` (v9.6.0)\n\n**Instantiation Pattern:**\n```typescript\nconst logger = pino({ level: process.env['LOG_LEVEL'] || 'info' });\n```\n\n**Logging Method Used Throughout:**\n- `logger.info(obj, msg)` - Information messages with context\n- `logger.warn(obj, msg)` - Warning messages \n- `logger.error({ err }, msg)` - Error messages with error objects\n- `logger.fatal(obj, msg)` - Fatal errors\n\n**Context Object Pattern (structured logging):**\n```typescript\n// With metadata object\nlogger.info({ workerId: config.workerId, orchestratorUrl: config.orchestratorUrl }, 'Configuration loaded');\n\n// With single property\nlogger.info({ port: config.httpPort }, 'HTTP API listening');\n\n// With error\nlogger.error({ err, executionId: msg.executionId }, 'Execution error');\n```\n\n**Files using logging (11 total in orchestrator, 5 in worker):**\n\nWorker package:\n- `/packages/worker/src/index.ts` - Main startup and shutdown logging\n- `/packages/worker/src/connection.ts` - Connection state, message handling\n- `/packages/worker/src/executor.ts` - Execution logging\n- `/packages/worker/src/parser.ts` - Parse events logging\n- `/packages/worker/src/cleanup.ts` - Cleanup operations\n\nOrchestrator package:\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts` - Startup, config, status checks\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/workerPool.ts` - Worker lifecycle\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts` - Execution dispatch\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/kafka.ts` - Kafka connection\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` - Database operations\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` - HTTP API logging\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts` - Event processing\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts` - Trigger scheduling\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/tokenManager.ts` - Token management\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/oauth.ts` - OAuth flow logging\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/gitlab.ts` - GitLab integration logging\n\n---\n\n### 3. **STRUCTURED LOGGING UTILITIES**\n\nNo dedicated logger utility module exists. Pino is used directly:\n\n- **Passed via constructor dependency injection** (all major classes accept `logger: Logger` parameter)\n- **Consistent naming:** Parameter always named `private logger: Logger`\n- **Type imported from pino:** `import type { Logger } from 'pino'`\n\nExamples:\n```typescript\n// connection.ts\nconstructor(\n  private orchestratorUrl: string,\n  private workerId: string,\n  private workerToken: string,\n  private callbacks: ConnectionCallbacks,\n  private logger: Logger,  // Injected logger\n) {}\n\n// workerPool.ts\nconstructor(\n  private expectedWorkerToken: string,\n  private logger: Logger,  // Injected logger\n) {}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **RECONNECTION LOGIC SUMMARY**\n\n**From connection.ts (Worker side):**\n\n1. **Initial Connection** (line 37-64):\n   - Sets `connected = true` on WebSocket open\n   - Sends 'hello' message with workerId, version, capabilities\n   - Starts heartbeat interval (30s)\n   - Logs success\n\n2. **Message Handling** (line 66-74):\n   - Parses binary message from orchestrator\n   - Routes to `handleMessage()` based on message type\n\n3. **Disconnection** (line 76-80):\n   - Logs close code and reason\n   - Calls `cleanup()` (clears heartbeat timer)\n   - Calls `scheduleReconnect()`\n\n4. **Reconnection Scheduling** (line 186-197):\n   - Uses exponential backoff: 1s → 2s → 4s → ... → 30s (max)\n   - Only reconnects if not shutting down\n   - Logs each reconnection attempt\n\n5. **Error Handling** (line 82-85):\n   - Logs WebSocket errors\n   - Notes that 'close' event will trigger reconnection\n\n**From workerPool.ts (Orchestrator side):**\n\n1. **Worker Registration** (line 103-146):\n   - Checks for duplicate worker IDs and disconnects old ones\n   - Stores worker info (version, capabilities, heartbeat time)\n   - Sets up heartbeat timer (30s interval, 90s timeout)\n   - Logs worker registration with metadata\n\n2. **Heartbeat Monitoring** (line 122-133):\n   - Monitors time since last heartbeat\n   - Closes connection if no heartbeat within 90s\n   - Sends heartbeat message to worker\n\n3. **Graceful Shutdown** (line 247-259):\n   - Sends shutdown message to all workers\n   - Allows 30s grace period\n   - Cleans up timers\n\n---\n\n### 5. **PROJECT STRUCTURE**\n\n**Root package.json:**\n- Monorepo with 3 workspaces: `packages/shared`, `packages/orchestrator`, `packages/worker`\n- Uses npm workspaces\n- TypeScript v5.7.0, tsx for development\n\n**Worker Package** (`/packages/worker`):\n- Dependencies: `ws`, `nanoid`, `pino`, `dotenv`, `@dac-cloud/shared`\n- Main entry: `src/index.ts`\n- Config: `src/config.ts` (loads `ORCHESTRATOR_URL`, `WORKER_TOKEN`, `WORKER_ID`)\n\n**Orchestrator Package** (`/packages/orchestrator`):\n- Dependencies: `ws`, `kafkajs`, `nanoid`, `pino`, `dotenv`, `better-sqlite3`, `@dac-cloud/shared`\n- Main entry: `src/index.ts`\n- Config: `src/config.ts` (loads master key, token, Kafka, Supabase JWT, ports)\n- Database: SQLite with better-sqlite3\n\n**Shared Package** (`/packages/shared`):\n- Exports types and protocol definitions\n- 25 TypeScript files total across all packages\n\n**TypeScript Config (tsconfig.base.json):**\n```json\n{\n  \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n  \"module\": \"NodeNext\",\n  \"moduleResolution\": \"NodeNext\",\n  \"strict\": true,\n  \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n  \"declaration\": true,\n  \"sourceMap\": true\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **.CLAUDE/SKILLS DIRECTORY**\n\n**File:** `cr.md` (6449 bytes)\n\n**Available Skill:** `/cr` - Code Review Skill\n- **Description:** Deep code review for security, performance, and code quality\n- **User Invocable:** Yes\n- **Performs:** Three-pass analysis (Security, Performance, Code Quality)\n- **Scope:** Reviews staged and unstaged changes, modified and untracked files\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Aspect | Finding |\n|--------|---------|\n| **Logger Library** | Pino v9.6.0 |\n| **Logger Pattern** | Dependency injection via constructor parameter |\n| **Context Format** | Structured object logging with metadata |\n| **Reconnection Strategy** | Exponential backoff (1s → 30s max) |\n| **Heartbeat Intervals** | Worker: 30s, Orchestrator: 30s (90s timeout) |\n| **WebSocket Libraries** | ws v8.18.0 (both worker & orchestrator) |\n| **Total TS Files** | 25 files across project |\n| **TypeScript Target** | ES2022, NodeNext module system |\n| **No Logger Utility** | Pino used directly; no wrapper module exists |\n\nAll logging uses **structu